(212, 1, '2016-03-18 02:46:17', '2016-03-18 02:46:17', '<div class="csRow">\r\n<div class="csColumn" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 64.1%;" data-csstartpoint="330" data-csendpoint="945" data-cswidth="64.1%" data-csid="261812bd-4f90-1937-ab85-8ee1f6b96215">\r\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;">HOW?</span></h2>\r\n<h3><span class="transcript ga" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="toc-video-transcript" data-duration="135.61">Step 1: Install OSX</span></h3>\r\n<h4>Launch OS X system recovery</h4>\r\nYou may already have OS X installed on your system. If so, feel free to move on to step two. However, if you have OS X installed but would like to encrypt your hard drive (assuming it is not already), you will need to go through the install again.\r\n\r\nIf the Mac already has a version of OS X installed, it is likely that it has a recovery partition. Turn on your mac and immediately press and hold the option key. This should show you the available drives you can boot from. Choose the recovery drive and skip to step 2.\r\n\r\nIf you have a completely blank hard drive in your mac you will need to use the internet recovery feature. Turn on your mac and immediately press and hold command + R. This will trigger the OS X internet recovery. This will take some time, most likely hours. Let the recovery finish downloading and proceed to step 2.\r\n<h4>Prepare the partition</h4>\r\nClick on the disk utility then select your hard drive from the left menu and hit erase. The interface will give you a few formatting options. For a simple, one system install, set the drive to either "OS X Extended (Journaled)" or "OS X Extended (Journaled, Encrypted)". For basecamp, dual-boot, multi-boot, and multi-partition installs check out this guide.\r\n\r\nNote: DO NOT choose a case sensitive file system. One of the main components of the system program stack is the Adobe Creative Cloud, which will not work on a case sensitive system.\r\n<h4>Install OSX</h4>\r\nExit the disk utility and now choose "Install OS X" from the menu.  Follow the instructions and log into your newly created profile.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Step 2: Configure Custom OS X Settings</h3>\r\n<h4>Change your desktop background</h4>\r\nkeyboard shortcut map\r\n<h4>Remove junk from the dock and set to autohide</h4>\r\nThere are a lot of items on the dock that you will not need. Drag the unnecessary apps off of the dock to remove them. My optimized dock looks like this:\r\n<p id="rbgppOK"><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec097f51c99-full.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-241 post-image" href="/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/_d_improd_/img_56ec097f51c99_f_improf_451x97.png" alt="" width="451" height="97" /></a></p>\r\nOnce you are done, hide the dock by pressing Cmd. + Opt. + D with the finder active.\r\n<h4>Configure OSX System Preferences</h4>\r\n<h5>General Settings</h5>\r\nI prefer the dark menu bar and graphite color scheme, but choose the settings that are best for you.\r\n<p id="kmUgvez"><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec09328bf0c-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-239 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec09328bf0c.png" alt="" /></a>￼￼</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Mission Control</h5>\r\n<p id="FhXQPUb"><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f194525d1fe-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-276 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f194525d1fe.png" alt="" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Security &amp; Privacy</h5>\r\nSeems to be set up properly already. This may be due to the partial manual transfer from the case-sensitive filesystem. Will have to check all of these settings again when a new install is preformed.\r\n<h5>Keyboard</h5>\r\nTurn on the smart quotes on the "text" tab and change the quotes to be the ones that are vertical only. These are code friendly quotes, and forcing some programs to use them will save you a lot of headache down the road.\r\n<p id="CdtrfOx"><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1967fe9bb9-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-280 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1967fe9bb9.png" alt="" /></a></p>\r\nWe will be replacing the spotlight in its entirety with Alfred 2. That being the case the command + space shortcut can be assigned to something you will use more often; the help search. First, lets change the current spotlight shortcut. I prefer to use command + option + space and disable the "show finder in search menu option".\r\n<p id="lcGahRK"><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec0edadc9c8-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-247 post-image" href="/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec0edadc9c8.png" alt="" /></a></p>\r\nYou will then want to click on the app shortcut tab on the left-hand side and assign the help search to command + space.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec0ef7b1754-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-249 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec0ef7b1754.png" alt="" /></a>\r\n<h5>Trackpad</h5>\r\nI like to enable all of the features that the trackpad has to offer. It may sound silly, but it is also easier on your fingertips if you use the tap to click instead of a press. I have also found that I like my trackpad sensitivity to be a bit higher than it is by default, but this is all just a matter of personal preference.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1984135a5e-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-282 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1984135a5e.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f198564e47c-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-284 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f198564e47c.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1986466f25-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-286 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1986466f25.png" alt="" /></a>\r\n<h4>Update Finder Settings</h4>\r\nWith the finder active (you can tell what app is active by the application name in the upper left corner next to the apple symbol) press cmd. + , (comma). This is the universal mac shortcut for opening the active applications settings. Update your finder settings to your liking. My preferred settings are displayed below.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec08f5e1d59-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-233 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec08f5e1d59.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec0900cf7cd-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-235 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec0900cf7cd.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec0909d57cc-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-237 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec0909d57cc.png" alt="" /></a>\r\n<h4>Update desktop view options</h4>\r\nUpdate your desktop view options to your liking. Below is an example of my preferred settings.\r\n<p id="yriLNft"><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec0a3d2e136-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-243 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec0a3d2e136.png" alt="" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Configure TextEdit Settings</h4>\r\nSet up your text edit settings to look like this. You will use this primarily for code and search and replace. Be sure to enable the smart quotes. We set these in the keyboard settings. This will for code friendly quotes, which will save you a lot of headache.\r\n<p id="anbAUfv"><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec05645ccc7-full.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-227 post-image alignnone" href="/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec05645ccc7.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec075fc1bf6-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-229 post-image" href="/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec075fc1bf6.png" alt="" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Increase Speed Of Mission Control Animations</h4>\r\n<p class="p1">Apples mission control gives you a lot of very intuitive options for organizing your desktops "spaces" and navigating between programs and windows. The one drawback I have found is that the animations are somewhat slow and unnecessary. The two links below will guide you on how to speed up the mission control animations, or disable them entirely.</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><a href="http://osxdaily.com/2012/02/14/speed-up-misson-control-animations-mac-os-x/"><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Speed Up Mission Control Animations in Mac OS X</span></a></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><a href="http://osxdaily.com/2012/03/28/change-dock-animation-speed-mac-os-x/">Change the Animation Speed of Hiding &amp; Displaying the Mac OS X Dock</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class="p1">Add Downloads Alias To Desktop</h4>\r\nAn "alias" on OS X is the same as a shortcut on widows. This is not a file itself, but an icon that points to the original file or folder. I like to have an alias of my downloads folder on my desktop for easy access. It is very easy to create an alias. In fact, you should be able to complete this task without ever touching your mouse.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hold down the command key and press tab to cycle through your open programs. Stop on the finder.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThere are a lot of keyboard shortcuts that make navigating around the finder very efficient. Soon we will install a program that will allow you to display a cheatsheet of all of them. For now, just follow along.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>With the finder active (you can tell which app is active from the name in the top left corner) press command + shift + H to open your home folder.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Note: there are a few different views available in the finder. I think the column view is by far the most efficient view. You can switch to the column view at any time by pressing command + 3.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Use the arrow keys to highlight your downloads folder and press command + L to create an alias. Press enter to accept the default name.</li>\r\n	<li>Press command + C to copy the alias to your clipboard, then press command + delete to move the original to the trash.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Note that this is necessary because OS X can copy files, but does not have the "cut" command by default.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Press command + shift + D to open your desktop in a finder window.</li>\r\n	<li>Press command + V to copy the alias to your desktop. Press return while the file is highlighted to edit the alias name, and remove "alias". Press return.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Configure OS X Not To Mount Certain Partitions On Start</h4>\r\nIf you are running a dual boot system like a bootcamp system, you may not want to even connect to the drive from your mac. If you need to prevent a drive or partition from mounting automatically upon system startup follow the guide below.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.cnet.com/how-to/prevent-a-partition-from-mounting-in-os-x/">Prevent a partition from mounting in OS X</a>\r\n<h3>Step 2: Install and Configure <a href="https://www.alfredapp.com/">Alfred 2</a></h3>\r\nAlfred is the single most powerful productivity app I have ever found. It acts much like the spotlight, but can be extended do much much more. There is a free version, but go ahead and buy the power pack. You will earn that money back in time saved 100x over.\r\n\r\nAlfred has may features built right out of the box. I would suggest just poking around each window of the settings to orient yourself. Below is a set of screenshots that show my preferred settings and options.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_251" align="aligncenter" width="500" class="imagepro-polaroid"]<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec166e131fc-full.png" target="_blank"><img class=" post-image wp-image-251" title="General Settings" href="/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/_d_improd_/img_56ec166e131fc_f_improf_500x320.png" alt="" width="500" height="320" data-imagepro-frames="imagepro-polaroid" /></a> I have found that double tap shift is a very effective way of calling the Alfred search bar. You can tap shift twice from either side of the keyboard, or simply reach back with you pinkies and hit both at the same time.[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_259" align="aligncenter" width="500" class="imagepro-polaroid"]<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec16d4e7a48-full.png"><img class="post-image wp-image-259" href="/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/_d_improd_/img_56ec16d4e7a48_f_improf_500x320.png" alt="" width="500" height="320" data-imagepro-frames="imagepro-polaroid" /></a> The web search pane controls all of the search engines that Alfred will connect to for you. There are quite a few useful entires by default. I like to truncate the keywords for the engines I use the most. Hitting "m" to jump to gmail and "d" to jump to drive will save you more time then you would expect. You can also add additional search functions. These will not do any sort of results-as-you type functionality, though this is available through some workflows[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_263" align="aligncenter" width="500" class="imagepro-polaroid"]<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec176ac1847-full.png"><img class="post-image wp-image-263" href="/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/_d_improd_/img_56ec176ac1847_f_improf_500x320.png" alt="" width="500" height="320" data-imagepro-frames="imagepro-polaroid" /></a> Alfred\'s clipboard history is a truly special thing. You can activate it by pressing alt + command + c. It will save a 24 hour history of your clipboard and display them by app. There is also a handy "snip" command you can use to permanently store the snipits you use most frequently.[/caption]\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec168d5a4e4-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-255 post-image" href="/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec168d5a4e4.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec16a30d304-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-257 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec16a30d304.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec170f3cf78-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-261 post-image" href="/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec170f3cf78.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec178758652-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-265 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec178758652.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec17c571a01-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-267 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56ec17c571a01.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f892b528101-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-364 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f892b528101.png" alt="" /></a>\r\n\r\nYou can also adjust the look and feel of Alfred by changing the theme. Try out the <a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/OctoCustom.alfredappearance.zip">OctoMarketing custom theme</a>.\r\n\r\nThe abilities of Alfred truly have no end when it comes to workflows. A workflow is a packet of code that will extend the functionality of Alfred. They are very easy to make, and there is a huge community of Alfred fans who have created hundreds of awesome workflows. If you think it should be possible just Google "urban dictionary search Alfred workflow".\r\n\r\nThere are a few essential workflows that I use all the time that I would recommend you install.\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.packal.org/workflow/secure-password-generator">Password Generator</a></h4>\r\nThis is a workflow that will easily generate long secure passwords for you. You can never be too careful when it comes to your cyber security. Use pwconf to configure the settings. A truly secure password is at least 25 characters using the full askII spectrum, but don\'t expect to ever remember such a password without a password management program like Dashlane or Lastpass (which I do recommend in step 3). pwgen will generate a random password for you.\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.packal.org/workflow/toggle-hidden-files">Toggle Hidden Files</a></h4>\r\nThis is a nifty little workflow that will allow you to toggle the "see hidden files" functionality of the finder off and on. Just type hidden. Most of the time you will want to leave hidden files hidden, but there are multiple instances where this tool will be nessecary.\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.alfredforum.com/topic/4097-type-not-paste-clipboard-workflow/">Type Not Paste Clipboard</a></h4>\r\nThis is another workflow that is here mainly to support your password management system. There are some protected password boxes that will not allow you to use the paste functionality. If you have exceedingly long passwords this can be very frustrating. Enter type not paste clipboard. I like to map the hot key to control + option + command + v. If you are ever having trouble pasting a password try using this.\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.alfredforum.com/topic/995-find-folder-— search-by-folder-name-workflow/">Folder Search</a></h4>\r\nAnother Alfred necessity. This workflow will limit your search results to only folders. By default queries will return all kinds of filetypes. If you know what you are looking for this can save you a lot of time. I like to truncate the search keyword to just "f".\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.alfredforum.com/topic/2249-hideunhide-desktop-icons/">Hide Desktop Icon</a></h4>\r\nUsually I keep my desktop pretty clean, but there are still some things that I would not want an audience to see if I were giving a presentation or recording a screencast. This workflow will help you quickly hide and unhide your desktop icons. Just type desktop hide or desktop unhide.\r\n<h4><a href="https://github.com/RyanVerhey/character-counter-alfred-workflow">Character Counter</a></h4>\r\nThere are all sorts of instances where you will want to know how many characters long something is. I like to set this workflow to use ct {query}\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.alfredforum.com/topic/2180-case-converter-including-title-case/">Case Converter</a></h4>\r\nConsistency is key if you are trying to make good branded content. The case converter will help you easily change the case style of any text. Just copy something from your clipboard like:\r\n\r\n4 ways that donald trump has angered octopi\r\n\r\nType "case" in Alfred. There should be a few formatting option available, like the title case. Highlight one and press return. The updated copy has now been copied to your clipboard.\r\n\r\n4 Ways That Donald Trump Has Angered Octopi\r\n<h4><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Chrome-Shortcuts.alfredworkflow.zip">Custom: Chrome Shortcuts</a></h4>\r\nThis is a custom workflow that we pulled together ourselves. The following commands will take you to the corresponding chrome browser screen.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ch b -Chrome bookmarks</li>\r\n	<li>ch e -Chrome extensions</li>\r\n	<li>ch a -Chrome apps</li>\r\n	<li>ch h -Chrome history</li>\r\n	<li>ch d -Chrome downloads</li>\r\n	<li>ch s -Chrome settings</li>\r\n	<li>ch store - Chrome store</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Custom-Chrome-Users.alfredworkflow.zip">Custom: Chrome Users</a></h4>\r\nYou can run into a lot of issues and frustrations if you are working with multiple Google accounts and you don\'t know how to properly manage them. This is a custom workflow designed by the OctoMarketing team that will help you manage multiple accounts and keep your work, business, and personal accounts from crossing streams. We will dive into how to do this further in step 4. Workflow shortcuts are as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ch personal - open personal Google Chrome account</li>\r\n	<li>ch work - open work Google Chrome account</li>\r\n	<li>ch business - open your business Google Chrome account</li>\r\n	<li>ch clean - open a Chrome account with no accounts, apps, or extensions</li>\r\n	<li>ch seo - open a Chrome account loaded with SEO analysis apps and extensions</li>\r\n	<li>ch web - open a Chrome account loaded with web development apps and extensions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Step 3: Install and Configure OS X App</h3>\r\n<h4><a href="https://creative.adobe.com/creative-cloud?promoid=NV3KR7S1&amp;mv=other">Adobe Creative Cloud Suite</a></h4>\r\nThe Adobe Creative Cloud is a full suite of web development and content creation software. Adobe Photoshop (photo editing), Illustrator (graphic design), Indesign (print documents), and Premier Pro (video editing), and many more tools are included in the package. Access to all of these tools is $49.99 a month, but the Adobe suite is a necessity for any web professional.\r\n<h4><a href="https://www.adobe.com/products/media-encoder.html">Adobe Media Encoder</a></h4>\r\nThis is just one of the apps available with the Creative Cloude Suite, but I thought it deserved a special callout, because it is much less known than some of the other apps. Adobe\'s media encoder is the most powerful mac encoder I have used by far. Convert anything to anything else. There are hundreds of presets for whatever your specific needs may be.\r\n<p id="cPvAQVo"><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8c68d72610-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-388 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8c68d72610.png" alt="" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><a href="https://www.trankynam.com/atext/">aText</a></h4>\r\nIf you haven\'t jumped on the text replacement bandwagon yet then you are in for a pleasant surprise. Almost any piece of test that you repeat on a consistent basis should be added to aText. Below are some shot of how I like to set up the preferences. aText is also a useful indicator when secure input is enabled. This usually happens when your are inputing a password and may mean that you cannot use copy and paste commands. In the Alfred section we install a type not paste clipboard workflow that addresses this limitation. Notice the flag on the aText icon indicating secure input on the second photo.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1ad7748544-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-298 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1ad7748544.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8dd03bf7cc-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-392 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8dd03bf7cc.png" alt="" /></a>\r\n<h4><a href="https://beamer-app.com/">Beamer</a></h4>\r\nIf you want to share your Macbook\'s screen wirelessly on another monitor, an apple tv / air play setup is probably what most mac users would gravitate to first. If you are only trying to steam content however, Beamer is definitely the better choice. The interface is simple and easy to use, the streaming technology is much more stable than airplay, it will play almost every video filetype, and it works seamlessly with the a Chromecast device as well as Apple Tv.\r\n<h4><a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/bettersnaptool/id417375580?mt=12#">Bettersnap Tool</a></h4>\r\nThe bettersnap tool is a mac app that allows us to snap windows around the screen with keyboard shortcuts. It also has a handy feature that will snap windows to the edge of the screen if you drag them to the edge of the screen. Below are the screenshots for my preferred settings and shortcuts.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1a1a4a3d87-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-290 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1a1a4a3d87.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1a1cb40acc-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-292 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1a1cb40acc.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1a6f025f0e-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-294 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1a6f025f0e.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1a72a750d3-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-296 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f1a72a750d3.png" alt="" /></a>\r\n<h4><a href="https://www.mediaatelier.com/CheatSheet/">CheatSheet</a></h4>\r\nCheatsheet is a tool that will assist you in your quest to be a true mac power user. Every app has lots of keyboard shortcuts to make your workflows more efficient. With CheatSheet just hold down the command key and an organized list of all of the apps shortcuts will be displayed.\r\n<p id="ppWPtPI"><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8b87fe30a1-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-368 post-image" href="/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8b87fe30a1.png" alt="" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><a href="https://panic.com/coda/">Coda 2</a></h4>\r\nCoda 2 is Panic\'s flagship product and is my favorite website development tool. Coda has a clean UI and is incredible functional. If you have ever thought that Dreamweaver seemed a bit to heavy and Muse was a bit too useless, then give Coda a try. Coda 2 is $99 for a single licence, and it\'s better than everything else.\r\n<h4><a href="https://www.google.com/chrome/">Google Chrome</a></h4>\r\nThe web professionals preferred browser. Google Chrome is widely accepted as the industry standard browser because of its ubiquity, stability, and huge library of apps and extensions. We will go through Chrome in depth in step 4. Do not discount the capabilities of other browsers however...\r\n<h4><a href="https://kapeli.com/dash">Dash</a></h4>\r\nDash is a massive repository of documentation for a huge variety of coding languages. Dash is extremely comprehensive and invaluable to any developer or aspiring learner. Dash has a large community behind it, and even connects to stack exchange for p-2-p documentation sharing. Dash integrates well with many of the web\'s most popular tools including Coda 2 and Alfred 2.\r\n<h4><a href="https://www.dashlane.com/">Dashlane</a></h4>\r\nDashlane is my favorite password management tool. It works consistently, is intuitive, and multi-platform. Dashlane will also help you manage credit cards, ID cards, software licenses, and more. Dashlane costs $39.99 a month.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8bb33e3ba0-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-372 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8bb33e3ba0.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8bb6f4b0fc-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-376 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8bb6f4b0fc.png" alt="" /></a>\r\n<h4><a href="http://Evernote">Evernote</a></h4>\r\nEvernote is one of the sleekest and most innovative note taking apps out there. Key features include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Categorize notes into notebooks</li>\r\n	<li>Attach PDFs and files to rich HTML notes</li>\r\n	<li>Easily annotate images</li>\r\n	<li>Chrome extension "web clipper" is the best website snipping tool I have found</li>\r\n	<li>Easily share notes and export to HTML</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><a href="http://flexibits.com/fantastical"> Fantastical</a></h4>\r\nFantastical is a very well designed and capable calendar and reminder application for mac devices. It comes with a high price tag, $50, but is definitely something you can live without if cost is a priority. I like to change the keyboard shortcut to control + space. This is a very quick and easy way to pull up a visual calendar for reference. You can even sync up your Google or Outlook calendar and search from the menu bar.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8bf29eda73-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-380 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8bf29eda73.png" alt="" /></a><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8bf8841a74-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-382 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8bf8841a74.png" alt="" /></a>\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.img2icnsapp.com/">Image2icon</a></h4>\r\nI just recently found this gem. Image2icon is a simple and easy tool for making sleek looking icons for in multiple styles and filetypes. It is an elegant balance between usability and customization. In modern web design it is imperative that there is consistency between your graphics. This tool makes that very very easy.\r\n<p id="yAHtmlZ"><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8c262b96de-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-386 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56f8c262b96de.png" alt="" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><a href="http://mplayerx.org/">MPlayerX</a></h4>\r\nEveryone love VLC Player, but in my opinion MPlayerX is second to none. This free media player will open damn near every media filetype out of the box and features easy playback speed control for audio and video with pitch correction. This means by tapping the ] key a few times while you are watching a tutorial video you can increase the playback speed. I like to watch my videos at about 200% speed. This used to be a difficult function to come by, but is much easier to accomplish with HTML5 video and is now supported by major video sites like Youtube and Lynda.com.\r\n<h4><a href="https://products.office.com/en-us/business/compare-office-365-for-business-plans">Microsoft Office 365 Business Premium</a></h4>\r\nWhen it comes to the office applications for small business there are really only two major players; Google Apps for work and Microsoft Office 365. An Apple iWork based IT stack is also feasible, but not as widely used. In a modern business environment this program suite will manage your email, cloud storage, documents, and much more. There are pros and cons to each stack which I have cover in depth in this comprehensive vendor review of the four top players in the market.\r\n\r\nIn a modern business environment it is very hard to operate without Microsoft office products like Word and Excel. With Office 365 Business Premium you get access to all of the office apps, 1TB of cloud storage space per user, and HD video conferencing through Skype. The cost is $12.50 a month per user, but is a fair price for what will be one of the pillars of your online business.\r\n<h4><a href="https://manytricks.com/moom/">Moom</a></h4>\r\nMoom is like a premium version of the better snap tool. Gain complete control over window placement on your Mac. This is particularly useful for multiple monitor set-ups. Imagine this: you want to see the a dashboard of multiple programs across your screens. Type in an Alfred commend that opens a series of applications and urls, log-in an authentication is taken care of automatically by Dashlane, Alfred then runs a Moom command that adjusts the placement of all of the apps at once across multiple screens, and all of this happens in under a second. Moom is not necessity if you have the bettersnap tool, but it can definitely help take power-users to the next level.\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.araelium.com/screenflick">Screenflick</a></h4>\r\nScreenflick is an excellent screen capture program for mac. Brand your videos, export in multiple formats, record internal and external audio, record and display keystrokes and presenter camera, the list goes on. If you have any need to create screencast videos this is the program for you.\r\n<h4><a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/sitesucker/id442168834?mt=12">Sitesucker</a></h4>\r\nEver see an awesome site and wish you could download and dissect it? Thats exactly what Sitesucker allows you to do. Be weary though, while downloading someone\'s site is not illegal blatantly copying the site is.\r\n<h4><a href="https://panic.com/transmit/">Transmit</a></h4>\r\nTransmit is a very functional and easy to use FTP client designed by Panic, the makers of Coda. I have used quite a few FTP clients and transmit is by far my favorite.\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.videolan.org/vlc/index.html">VLC Player</a></h4>\r\nA free, awesome, and widely supported media player. It\'s like iTunes doppelganger that doesn\'t suck.\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16832416892&amp;cm_re=windows_10-_-32-416-892-_-Product">Microsoft Windows 10 Home</a></h4>\r\nThere may be instances were you want to run a virtual windows machine, or boot from a Windows partition of your mac. To do this you will need two things; a Windows os install, and Vmware Fusion.\r\n\r\nThe windows partition can be installed using Apple\'s Bootcamp software. If you want to install windows on your system follow this guide to get started.\r\n<h4><a href="http://store.vmware.com/store/vmware/en_US/pd/productID.323689100?src=WWW_eBIZ_productpage_Fusion_Buy_US">VMware Fusion 8</a></h4>\r\nVMware Fusion is an awesome virtual machine management program designed specifically for mac and bootcamp. Fusion will allow you to start up your windows partition as a virtual machine, so you don\'t have to decide between a virtual machine or boot partition, and you don\'t need to restart your computer to launch and edit your bootcamp machine.\r\n<h3>Step 4: Install and Configure Chrome Clients And Extension Stacks</h3>\r\nRemember when we created the chrome user Alfred workflow and I told you we would circle back around to finish Chrome setup later? Its that time. As a refresher, type "ch " into your Alfred search bar and review the different commands we have programmed in. There should be five chrome users from the Octo Chrome Users workflow. They are personal, word, business, clean, seo, and web.\r\n\r\nNow let\'s talk a little bit about how Google and Chrome handle accounts, Chrome profiles, and browsers. When you sign up for a personal Google account you automatically gain access to all of Google\'s services and apps and can log in with your Google account credentials. The username for your Google account is your Gmail address. You may not use this address much if your are running on an Office 365 stack, but if that is the case you will at least want to forward the address to your primary one so that you can still receive important alerts and notifications from Google about your account.\r\n\r\nYou can review your entire Google account as a whole by going to <a href="http://myaccount.google.com">myaccount.google.com</a>. If you have had a Google account for a while also check out <a href="http://passwords.google.com">passwords.google.com</a>. You will be amazed at how much Google has collected. Your personal google account is attached to your email, your drive, your calendar, youtube, everything google.\r\n\r\nIf you are working with Google Apps For work, the major alternative to office 365, then you will have an admin account that will be able to manage users and company settings from admin.google.com. You will be able to connect your domain for branded emails like tim@coolcompany.com which will serve as the email credential for the users Google account.\r\n\r\nA Google account can also be used to log in to Google Chrome. If you go to the Google Chrome Settings ("ch s" in Alfred or command + , on mac) at the top of the screen you will see an option to sign in. When you sign into Chrome, Google will save and sync all of your chrome data like bookmarks and extensions.\r\n\r\nOnce you log in to Chrome you should also see your google account show up in the "people" area of the settings window. I think the term "people" is a bit confusing, so I will refer to them as profiles. Chrome people = chrome profiles\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56fa865edef1b-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-399 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56fa865edef1b.png" alt="" /></a>\r\n\r\nEach chrome browser can have multiple profiles and can log into any Google account even without creating a Chrome profile. You can even log one profile into the Chrome browser and then log into a different Google account. We will talk about when you may want to do this in a bit. The Chrome browser can only be logged into one Google account at a time however, and that is across all Google apps. Want to access your gmail and your clients Youtube profile in the same window? That could be a problem.\r\n\r\nWhat you would want to do instead is press command + n to open a new Chrome window, click on the profile name in the top right corner of the Chrome window, switch to a different chrome profile, and then log into your client\'s Youtube. The chrome profile you use can be one specifically for your client, or any other; you just can\'t log in using the same Chrome profile. You could have a chrome profile that is just "client" or "client4" if you are frequently working on multiple Google accounts at the same time. This all may sound a bit confusing, but the Octo Chrome Users Alfred workflow we installed earlier makes everything much easier to manage.\r\n\r\nWhen you run a Chrome user command from Alfred for the first time, a profile folder is created in the Chrome applications support folder, and should launch a new Chrome window. For more on how the workflow works and how to customize it, check out this article. Note that the chrome profile will say something like "person 2" until you log in to Chrome or change it manually.\r\n\r\nUse the Alfred Commands to open the personal chrome profile. Log into your personal Google account in the Chrome settings then log into your Gmail or another Google app. Now when you type "ch p" into your Alfred you will call up a Chrome window that is logged into your personal Google account and chrome account. The work account is intended for those who want a day job profile, and the business profile is for the Google account that you use to manage your own business. You may not have a Google account for your business yet. That is not a problem, but check out this guide if you want to jump ahead and get your business google account set up. If you plan on using either of these profiles, log them into both Gmail and Chrome now using their corresponding Alfred profiles.\r\n\r\nNow what about "ch seo" and "ch web"? Those don\'t really sound like users. What these Chrome profiles do is leverage the fact that each chrome profile has its own extensions. There are thousands of useful Chrome extension and apps for all sorts of purposed on the chrome web store. Type "ch store" into your browser to check them out. I have compiled a full list of my favorite extension here for you, but don\'t go all willy nilly and install all of these on your personal profile. You would have such a bloated browser you could revert to IE speeds...\r\n<p id="iDlokPo"><a href="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56fa8f99a3d24-full.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-402 post-image" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/img_56fa8f99a3d24.png" alt="" /></a></p>\r\nInstead we will be installing browser stacks. A stack is a set of technologies that work in tandem to accomplish a goal. This guide is helping you set up a variety of different stacks that will work together. A Mac App stack, a cloud stack, and now Chrome stacks. We will install all of the SEO plugins on the SEO profile so that we have fast and easy access to all of the powerful SEO extensions without having to bog down our other profiles. The web chrome profile will be loaded with a bunch of tools that will assist you greatly in web development.\r\n\r\nYou can see using this method we can call different chrome windows for specific users and google profiles, and we can also call chrome browsers that are more geared toward a specific use case and have a specific browser stack installed. You do not need to create a Google account for your use case browsers like SEO and web, but you may want to anyway to leverage chrome\'s syncing abilities.\r\n\r\nIf you need to do some SEO analysis or web work on your business or a client, don\'t be afraid to log into their google account using the SEO or web browser. Just don\'t sign the Chrome browser into another account.\r\n\r\nBelow is a map of the all of the Chrome extensions that I like to use and how I lay out my extension stacks per profile. You can read more about all of the chrome extensions here. Go through and install all of your chrome extensions now. Note that many extensions will appear in the chrome menu that are not needed. You can right click those items and hit "hide". Examples of cleaned up menu bars for the business, seo, and web profiles are below.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="embed">[embeddoc url="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/chrome_stacks.xlsx" download="all" viewer="microsoft"]</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="csColumnGap" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 3.12%;"><img style="border: none;" src="http://localhost/octomarketing.com/wp-content/plugins/advanced-wp-columns/assets/js/plugins/views/img/1x1-pixel.png" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div class="csColumn" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 31.3%;" data-csstartpoint="15" data-csendpoint="315" data-cswidth="31.3%" data-csid="46ed88e8-ab6c-1254-a760-36e1edf373d3">\r\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;">WHAT?</span></h2>\r\nThis system will guide you through how prepare an OS X system for use as a marketing and web development power user. The guide will cover setup and installation of the OS, installing programs, modifying settings, and programming shortcuts. By the time you are done the Mac should be optimized for a number of marketing and web development workflows. This guide follow many security best practices to ensure that your business is security is locked down from the start.\r\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;">WHY?</span></h2>\r\nOut of the box OS X is missing many of the capabilities you will need to successfully market your business online. This guide will give you all the tools you will need to accomplish the tasks you will face. It will also make using the mac operating system much more efficient.\r\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;">WHO?</span></h2>\r\nThis should be done by whoever is going to be using the system. Don\'t have a tech savvy friend or relative do this for you. Having an understanding of how your system works and is set up is a key aspect of being a power user. Like a jedi padawan, you must build your own lightsaber.\r\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;">WHEN?</span></h2>\r\nIf you are just starting up your business and want an optimized system to start out (highly recommended), then this is one of the first things you will do. If you are part of an agency or team you may need to do this every time you have a new hire. If done efficiently the whole process should take about four hours.\r\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;">HOW MUCH?</span></h2>\r\nThis example will use a 15" macbook pro, that will be upgraded with a 1TB SSD and 16gb of ram. Installation of the hard drive and ram is covered in this article. The total cost of this equipment is about $1100.\r\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;">WITH WHAT?</span></h2>\r\n<span class="transcript ga" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="toc-video-transcript" data-duration="194.99">Paste finished resource grid here.</span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div style="clear: both; float: none; display: block; visibility: hidden; width: 0px; font-size: 0px; line-height: 0;"></div>\r\n</div>', 'System Setup For New Mac Installs: OSX El Capitan', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'system-setup-for-new-mac-installs-osx-el-capitan', '', '', '2016-04-01 05:28:59', '2016-04-01 05:28:59', '', 0, 'http://www.octomarketing.com/?post_type=operations_handbook&#038;p=212', 0, 'operations_handbook', '', 0) ;
